<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The code reads from record->name_entry via a non-const pointer: record is declared as OS_common_record_t *record but is only used for read-only access (copying the name). According to Rule 8.13 the pointer should point to a const-qualified type whenever possible, e.g. declare record as const OS_common_record_t *record (or make name_entry a const char[] / const char *). As written the source buffer is not const-qualified, violating the intent of Rule 8.13.
</scenario>

